text: Milledgeville is a city in and the county seat of Baldwin County in the U.S. state of Georgia. It is northeast of Macon and bordered on the east by the Oconee River. The population of the town of Milledgeville was 17,070 at the 2020 census. ==References== Category:Cities in Georgia (U.S. state) Category:County seats in Georgia
title: Milledgeville, Georgia
